    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@soltanmm, I think this is very separable from everything else that we're doing. The version number is currently encoded in setup.py, right? Is there a way to make it accessible from inside the code? What if we moved it into the code itself; could setup.py find it there?\n\nI think the legacy libraries do something smart with not-replicating-the-version-number-thither-and-yon; we may want to follow what they do.\n"
